<div id="review_14211906" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/14211906" />
    <a title="Liz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/840833-liz"><img alt="Liz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1488918630p2/840833.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/14211906?book_show_action=true">Jan 31, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Liz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Liz" href="/user/show/840833-liz">Liz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Everyone</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer14211906" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17879186358706128799">This 5th volume covers a very short time period in LDS church history. The saints had just been forced to leave Missouri or face more brutal atacks. The Governer had issued the &quot;extermination order&quot; and they were forced at gun point to leave everything they had. They settled in Illinois and soon founded the beautiful city of Nauvoo from what was once only a swamp. <br/><br/>I really enjoy these books because they use real church history to tell the story of the restoration and the Steed family are really </span>
  <span id="freeText17879186358706128799" style="display:none">This 5th volume covers a very short time period in LDS church history. The saints had just been forced to leave Missouri or face more brutal atacks. The Governer had issued the "extermination order" and they were forced at gun point to leave everything they had. They settled in Illinois and soon founded the beautiful city of Nauvoo from what was once only a swamp. <br /><br />I really enjoy these books because they use real church history to tell the story of the restoration and the Steed family are really fun to follow. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17879186358706128799" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
